snippet.textDisplay:
Boyd my man! Love to see my favorite tubers do "current affairs" videos.


Bonus info for bump starting your car: It actually works in reverse as well! And due to the gear ratio you don't have to push as quickly! Which means, you can basically stay seated and (with right hand drive cars) have your left foot already on the clutch, and push the car backwards with just the right foot hanging out the door. Makes it safer too, you don't have to jump into a moving car.


Ultimate protip: If you already know about your battery being shitty, try to find a decline to park on, so you can just make gravity do the pushing!
